      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: channel echo / session pinning",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Adds echo delivery infrastructure that mirrors session messages to additional channels\n- `SessionEchoTarget` type on `SessionEntry` for persistent echo target configuration\n- `message:sent` internal hook triggers echo delivery (fire-and-forget, no circular echo)\n- CLI: `openclaw sessions echo add/remove/list` subcommands\n- Gateway method: `sessions.echo` for programmatic pin/unpin (VituReClaw HUD)\n\n## Motivation\n\nSessions used across multiple transports (Telegram + VituReClaw glasses + web UI) result in fragmented chat logs. Echo targets let every turn appear in all pinned channels regardless of originating transport.\n\n## Files changed\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|--------|\n| `src/config/sessions/types.ts` | `SessionEchoTarget` type + `echoTargets` field |\n| `src/infra/outbound/echo.ts` | Core echo resolution + delivery |\n| `src/infra/outbound/echo-hook.ts` | Internal hook registration |\n| `src/commands/sessions-echo.ts` | CLI subcommands |\n| `src/gateway/server-methods/sessions.ts` | `sessions.echo` gateway method |\n| `src/gateway/server-methods.ts` | Method registration |\n| `src/gateway/server-startup-post-attach.ts` | Hook auto-registration at boot |\n| `src/cli/program/register.status-health-sessions.ts` | CLI command wiring |\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [ ] Unit test for `resolveEchoTargets` (deduplication, role filtering)\n- [ ] Integration test: add echo target via gateway method, send message, verify echo arrives\n- [ ] Verify circular echo prevention (echo delivery does not re-trigger hooks)\n- [ ] CLI smoke test: add/list/remove echo targets\n\nSupersedes #88386 (closed: branch had unrelated deployment commits).",
